CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, November 8, 1958, pg. B12 reads: "Wins Trophy - Mary Jean Shipman Brown holds the first-prize trophy she won in fashion designing, in the annual fashion show, "Behind the Green Door," sponsored by the Club Unique. She designs and makes her entire wardrobe under a patented label, "Marie Jeanne Originals." - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Mary Jean Shipman Brown wearing Swiss dot top, holding first prize trophy for fashion design during Club Unique's "Behind the Green Door" fashion show, seated in front of landscape patterned curtain
